Data availability

            All data supporting the findings of this study are available from public repositories. Observed precipitation data from HadEX3 and IMERG V07 were downloaded from the Met Office HadEX3 portal (https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/hadobs/hadex3/) and GPM-IMERG dataset page of NASA (https://disc.gsfc.nasa.gov/datasets/GPM-3IMERGDF_07/summary), respectively. HighResMIP and CMIP6 model outputs are available via the ESGF node (https://esgf-node.llnl.gov/search/cmip6/). ECMWF ERA5 reanalysis data can be accessed at https://www.ecmwf.int/en/forecasts/dataset/ecmwf-reanalysis-v5. As part of this study, we are releasing the ten-member CESM-HR ensembles of historical-and-future transient climate simulations (1920–2100), which are available through the NSF NCAR Geoscience Data Exchange (GDEX) platform at https://gdex.ucar.edu/datasets/d651007/ (historical ensemble)64, https://gdex.ucar.edu/datasets/d651008/ (RCP 6.0 future ensemble)65 and https://gdex.ucar.edu/datasets/d651009/ (RCP 8.5 future ensemble)66.
          Code availability

            The MOAAP code are available via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7561616 (ref. 67). The CESM codes are available via GitHub at https://github.com/ihesp/cesm/tree/ihesp-hires-master.
